deselectInst(25.10)                                        deselectInst(25.10)

Name
       deselectInst - Deselects the specified instance

Syntax
        deselectInst

       [-help]

       instName

       Deselects the specified instance. Once an instance is deselected, it is
       no  longer  highlighted  in the design display window. Use this command
       after selecting one or more instances.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for each deselectInst parameter. For a detailed de-
              scription of the command and all of its parameters, use the  man
              command:

              man deselectInst

       <instName>
              Specifies the name(s) of the instance(s).

              Data_type: (inst)+, required

Examples
              * The following command deselects the inst named inst_1:

                deselectInst inst_1

              *
                 The  following  command  deselects the insts named inst_2 and
                inst_3:

                deselectInst {inst_2 inst_3}

Related Information
              * selectInst

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

